FT  07 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Helene rises 31% at midway
Helene, the fashion wear manufacturer, reported pre-tax profits up 31 per
cent at Pounds 1.28m for the first half of 1994, against Pounds 975,000. The
group said the main operating companies made good advances.
Operating profits of Pounds 2.14m (Pounds 1.51m) were helped by a Pounds
250,000 insurance claim. A further Pounds 500,000 is expected shortly.
Turnover was Pounds 51.8m (Pounds 45.9m). Earnings per share were 0.62p
(0.56p) and the interim dividend is unchanged at 0.65p.
Since the period end Reggie &amp; Co has been acquired for up to Pounds 10m and
Pounds 14.9m raised by a rights and share subscription.
